 serializable one? That way, in.readObject will deserialize it, requiring reflection, which could record the call site and then cause a ClassCastException. But this would be a broken negative path, not officially supported. I recall the rules say exception assertions are only acceptable for documented paths. Hmm, maybe I could catch the ClassCastException in a test? An alternative could involve using an ObjectOutputStream subclass to override writeObject.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test modifications**\\n\\nI’m trying to figure out if we need to modify the tests to prove something specific. I wonder if adding a test that uses `ObjectOutputStream.PutField` would help, but it doesn't seem right. Then I think about using `setPointFormat`, but that doesn't feel like the answer either. I even consider using an ASN1 encoding object, but again, I’m not convinced that's the right direction. So, I’m really unsure about what modifications are needed.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating modifications and tests**\\n\\nI’m starting to think that the attempt count might not accurately reflect the modifications. It seems the coverage didn’t re-run after those changes, which is an issue if it indicates two attempts that are actually none. I’ll consider adding a test that utilizes serialization through BouncyCastle’s KeyFactory and the public API to produce a BCECPublicKey, possibly using KeyPairGenerator. I need to ensure BouncyCastleProvider is properly initialized, or the tests could fail.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering provider registration**\\n\\nTo prevent any provider registration issues, I think using a direct constructor is the way to go. I might also consider adding KeyFactory from the encoded original along with `new BouncyCastleProvider`. That seems like it could help. Additionally, it might be wise to check if the `BCECPublicKey` serialization behavior is currently behaving as expected. This leads me to wonder if I should assert whether `ObjectStreamClass.lookup(BCECPublicKey.class).hasWriteObjectMethod()` is returning true, particularly regarding any private methods.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_STNaPHWXjqcI0Auc1TiZsfZU|fc_0e9f35094975ac74016a25c439b39c8197be89a0d515f3d5a2", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk18on/BCECPublicKeyTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.security.spec.ECPublicKeySpec;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n", "newText": "import java.security.spec.ECPublicKeySpec;\n\nimport javax.crypto.Cipher;\nimport javax.crypto.KeyGenerator;\nimport javax.crypto.SealedObject;\nimport javax.crypto.SecretKey;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void signedObjectSerializesAndRestoresEcPublicKey() throws Exception {\n        ECPublicKey original = newBcEcPublicKey();\n        KeyPair signingKeyPair = newSigningKeyPair();\n        Signature signingSignature = Signature.getInstance(\"SHA256withRSA\");\n\n        SignedObject signedObject = new SignedObject(original, signingKeyPair.getPrivate(), signingSignature);\n\n        assertThat(signedObject.verify(\n                signingKeyPair.getPublic(),\n                Signature.getInstance(\"SHA256withRSA\"))).isTrue();\n        assertRestoredKeyMatchesOriginal(original, (ECPublicKey)signedObject.getObject());\n    }\n\n    private static BCECPublicKey newBcEcPublicKey() {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void unsharedSerializationRestoresEcPublicKey() throws Exception {\n        ECPublicKey original = newBcEcPublicKey();\n\n        ECPublicKey restored = deserializeUnshared(serializeUnshared(original));\n\n        assertRestoredKeyMatchesOriginal(original, restored);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void signedObjectSerializesAndRestoresEcPublicKey() throws Exception {\n        ECPublicKey original = newBcEcPublicKey();\n        KeyPair signingKeyPair = newSigningKeyPair();\n        Signature signingSignature = Signature.getInstance(\"SHA256withRSA\");\n\n        SignedObject signedObject = new SignedObject(original, signingKeyPair.getPrivate(), signingSignature);\n\n        assertThat(signedObject.verify(\n                signingKeyPair.getPublic(),\n                Signature.getInstance(\"SHA256withRSA\"))).isTrue();\n        assertRestoredKeyMatchesOriginal(original, (ECPublicKey)signedObject.getObject());\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void sealedObjectSerializesAndRestoresEcPublicKey() throws Exception {\n        ECPublicKey original = newBcEcPublicKey();\n        SecretKey secretKey = newAesKey();\n        Cipher sealingCipher = Cipher.getInstance(\"AES\");\n        sealingCipher.init(Cipher.ENCRYPT_MODE, secretKey);\n\n        SealedObject sealedObject = new SealedObject(original, sealingCipher);\n\n        Cipher openingCipher = Cipher.getInstance(\"AES\");\n        openingCipher.init(Cipher.DECRYPT_MODE, secretKey);\n        assertRestoredKeyMatchesOriginal(original, (ECPublicKey)sealedObject.getObject(openingCipher));\n    }\n\n    private static BCECPublicKey newBcEcPublicKey() {\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static KeyPair newSigningKeyPair() throws Exception {\n        KeyPairGenerator keyPairGenerator = KeyPairGenerator.getInstance(\"RSA\");\n        keyPairGenerator.initialize(2048);\n        return keyPairGenerator.generateKeyPair();\n    }\n\n    private static void assertRestoredKeyMatchesOriginal(ECPublicKey original, ECPublicKey restored) {\n", "newText": "    private static KeyPair newSigningKeyPair() throws Exception {\n        KeyPairGenerator keyPairGenerator = KeyPairGenerator.getInstance(\"RSA\");\n        keyPairGenerator.initialize(2048);\n        return keyPairGenerator.generateKeyPair();\n    }\n\n    private static SecretKey newAesKey() throws Exception {\n        KeyGenerator keyGenerator = KeyGenerator.getInstance(\"AES\");\n        keyGenerator.init(128);\n 